Chapter 6, Figure 3

Packages

library(rcapso)

Requirements

  1. The QtCapso program.
  2. The rcapso package.

Procedure

  1. Simulate a local CaPso model on a lattice of \(512 \times 512\) cells, during 40 seasons, using the following parameters.
{
    "competitionFactor": 0,
    "finalInertiaWeight": 0,
    "fitnessRadius": 1,
    "initialInertiaWeight": 0,
    "initialNumberOfPredators": 2621,
    "initialNumberOfPreys": 1,
    "predatorCognitiveFactor": 0,
    "predatorMaximumSpeed": 1,
    "predatorReproductionRadius": 1,
    "predatorReproductiveCapacity": 1,
    "predatorSocialFactor": 0,
    "predatorSocialRadius": 1,
    "preyReproductionRadius": 1,
    "preyReproductiveCapacity": 0,
    "type": "LOCAL"
}
  1. Load the results of the simulation in a dataframe.
sim <- read.csv("~/Documents/Datasets/capso/code_test/pcg_fig_6_3_a_ez_1_0_0.csv")
sim <- sim1[, c("Preys", "Predators")]
head(sim1)
  1. Plot the time series of preys and predators.
rcapso_plot_prey_pred_data(sim)

  1. Repeat the simulation using a predatorReproductiveCapacity equal to 5. Load the results in a dataframe.
sim <- read.csv("~/Documents/Datasets/capso/code_test/pcg_fig_6_3_a_ez_5_0_0.csv")
sim <- sim[, c("Preys", "Predators")]
head(sim)
  1. Plot the time series of preys and predators.
rcapso_plot_prey_pred_data(sim, normalize = TRUE)

  1. Compute a CaPso mean field model, where the only active transition functions are the reproduction of predators, the death of predators and the death of preys, during 40 seasons using the following parameters:
    • num_iter = 1
    • use_reg = TRUE
    • psi0 = 1
    • phi0 = 0.01
    • ey = 1
    • ry = 1
    • ez = 1
    • rz = 1
rules <- c("rep_preds", "death_preds", "death_preys")
df1   <- rcapso_compute_mf(rules, num_iter = 40, use_reg = TRUE, psi0 = 1, phi0 = 0.01, ez = 1, rz = 1)
head(df1)
  1. Repeat the previous step but use ez = 5.
df5   <- rcapso_compute_mf(rules, num_iter = 40, use_reg = TRUE, psi0 = 1, phi0 = 0.01, ez = 5, rz = 1)
head(df5)
  1. Plot both results
rcapso_plot_prey_pred_data(df1)

rcapso_plot_prey_pred_data(df5)

Results

  • Verify that the plots match the data in Figure 6.3.
